|YK0#|YKB Guild Combinations|000

|GK0You may hold at most two learned guilds, and a second guild opens at
level 50. Both guilds must accept the pairing; race, allegiance, and each
guild's own joining requirements still apply. Classes describe what a
character innately is and are not part of the dual-guild system.|000

|YK0##|YKB The groups|000

|CKBNeutral:|000  Bard, Berserker, Charlatan, Fighter, Psionicist,
           Street Samurai, Swashbuckler
|CKBGaea:|000     Druid, Garou, Lunar, Ninja
|CKBMitra:|000    Cleric of Mitra, Mage, Paladin
|CKBSet:|000      Priest, Thief

|YK0##|YKB What pairs with what|000

|GK0Neutral guilds|000 pair with each other and with any Gaea, Mitra, or
Set guild -- with one exception: |CKBStreet Samurai|000. The Gaea guilds
will not take one whose flesh is threaded with chrome, and no street
samurai will kneel to the green. Street samurai may still pair with the
other neutrals and with the Mitra and Set guilds.

|GK0Gaea guilds|000 (Druid, Garou, Lunar, Ninja) pair with each other and
with the neutral guilds except Street Samurai. In addition:
|BKB* |CKBGarou|000 may also pair with |CKBThief|000 and |CKBRanger|000.

|GK0Mitra guilds|000 (Cleric of Mitra, Mage, Paladin) pair with each other
and with all seven neutral guilds. They do not mix with Gaea or Set.

|GK0Set guilds|000 (Priest, Thief) pair with each other and with all seven
neutral guilds. Thief may also pair with |CKBGarou|000.

|GK0Ranger|000 pairs only with |CKBGarou|000.

|YK0##|YKB Solo guilds|000

|GK0Dragon, Monk, Morpher, Necro, Vampire, and BloodMage walk alone: their
disciplines permit no second guild.|000

|GK0BattleMage, Deathknight, Glyph, and UberGarou are special orders with
their own entry requirements -- ask their halls, not this list.|000

